ount Leopold Berchtold]], Austrian-Hungarian politician and diplomat, [[List of foreign ministers of Austria-Hungary|Joint Foreign Minister of Austria-Hungary]] (d. 1942) * 1863 &ndash; [[Linton Hope]], English sailor and architect (d. 1920) *[[1864]] &ndash; [[Richard Harding Davis]], American journalist and author (d. 1916) *[[1874]] &ndash; [[Ivana Brlić-Mažuranić]], Croatian author and poet (d. 1938) *[[1877]] &ndash; [[Vicente Sotto]], Filipino lawyer and politician (d. 1950) *[[1879]] &ndash; [[Korneli Kekelidze]], Georgian philologist and scholar (d. 1962) *[[1880]] &ndash; [[Sam Crawford]], American baseball player, coach, and umpire (d. 1968) *[[1882]] &ndash; [[Isaac Babalola Akinyele]], Nigerian ruler (d. 1964) * 1882 &ndash; [[Leopold Stokowski]], English conductor (d. 1977) *[[1884]] &ndash; [[Jaan Anvelt]], Estonian educator and politician (d. 1937) *[[1888]] &ndash; [[Duffy Lewis]], American baseball player, coach, and manager (d. 1979) *[[1889]] &ndash; [[Jessie Street]], Australian activist (d. 1970)<ref>{{cite web |last1=Radi |first1=Heather |title=Street, Lady Jessie Mary (1889–1970) |url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/street-lady-jessie-mary-11789 |website=Australian Dictionary of Biography |publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University |accessdate=9 February 2020}}</ref> *[[1892]] &ndash; [[Eugene Houdry]], French-American mechanical engineer and inventor (d. 1962) *[[1893]] &ndash; [[Violette Morris]], French shot putter and discus thrower (d. 1944) *[[1897]] &ndash; [[Ardito Desio]], Italian geologist and cartographer (d. 2001) * 1897 &ndash; [[Per-Erik Hedlund]], Swedish skier (d. 1975) *[[1898]] &ndash; [[Patrick Hennessy (industrialist)|Patrick Hennessy]], Irish soldier and businessman (d. 1981) *[[1900]] &ndash; [[Bertha Isaacs]], Bahamian teacher, tennis player, politician and women's rights activist (d. 1997)<ref>{{cite web|ref={{harvid|Womens Suffrage Bahamas|2012}}|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|ti