ch]], American novelist and short story writer * 1945 &ndash; [[Robert Bausch]], American novelist and short story writer *[[1946]] &ndash; [[Hayley Mills]], English actress<ref name="bell">{{cite book |last1=Bell |first1=Mary Hayley |title=What Shall We Do Tomorrow? |date=1968 |publisher=Cassell & Co. LTD. |pages=180-182}}</ref> * 1946 &ndash; [[Tommy Shannon]], American bass guitarist *[[1947]] &ndash; [[Moses Blah]], Liberian general and politician, 23rd [[President of Liberia]] (d. 2013) * 1947 &ndash; [[Dorothy Lyman]], American actress * 1947 &ndash; [[Cindy Pickett]], American actress * 1947 &ndash; [[Jerzy Stuhr]], Polish actor, director, and screenwriter * 1947 &ndash; [[James Woods]], American actor and producer *[[1948]] &ndash; [[Régis Wargnier]], French director, producer, and screenwriter *[[1949]] &ndash; [[Geoff Bodine]], American race car driver *[[1950]] &ndash; [[Paul Callery]], Australian footballer * 1950 &ndash; [[Tina Chow]], American model and jewelry designer (d. 1992) * 1950 &ndash; [[Kenny Ortega]], American director, producer, and choreographer * 1950 &ndash; [[Grigory Sokolov]], Russian pianist and composer *[[1951]] &ndash; [[Ricardo Fortaleza]], Australian-Filipino boxer and coach * 1951 &ndash; [[Pierre Pettigrew]], Canadian businessman and politician, 5th [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Canada)|Canadian Minister of Foreign Affairs]] *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Rick Moranis]], Canadian-American actor, comedian, singer and screenwriter *[[1954]] &ndash; [[Robert Greenberg]], American pianist and composer *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Eric Roberts]], American actor *[[1957]] &ndash; [[Ian Campbell (athlete)|Ian Campbell]], Australian jumper *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Gabi Delgado-López]], Spanish-German singer, co-founder of [[Deutsch Amerikanische Freundschaft|D.A.F.]] * 1958 &ndash; [[Malcolm Marshall]], Barbadian cricketer and coach (d. 1999) *[[1959]] &ndash; [[Susan Faludi]], American journalist and author * 1959 &ndash; [[Frank Mulholland, Lord Mulholland]